description: Since 2010, several hundred Comorians have died at sea while trying to reach the French overseas territory of Mayotte. A joint investigation by Le Monde and Lighthouse Reports shows that police maneuvers are implicated in several of these shipwrecks.

Nestlé says chairman Paul Bulcke to step down
description: Bulcke, who has been scheduled to remain in his position until next April, said in a statement on Tuesday that he had 'full trust in Nestlé's new leadership' after Nespresso CEO Philipp Navratil was appointed to take over by his fellow board members.

headline: Suspect in Charlie Kirk killing charged with murder, Utah seeks death penalty
description: Authorities said Tyler Robinson, 22, used a rifle to shoot the conservative political activist with a single bullet to the neck from a rooftop on September 10. Robinson is facing six other charges, including obstruction of justice and witness tampering. Utah County Attorney Jeff Gray told a press conference that he is seeking the death penalty.

headline: The Bayeux Tapestry, a barometer of Franco-British relations
description: France's decision to lend the nearly 1,000-year-old tapestry to the United Kingdom represents part of the long and tumultuous relationship between the two countries; Brexit supporters had even turned the tapestry into a symbol of national humiliation.

headline: Francesca Albanese, a critical Western voice on Gaza
description: At a conference at a left-wing festival near Paris, the UN special rapporteur on the occupied Palestinian territories received a standing ovation after denouncing European governments' inaction over Israel's destruction of Gaza. Her stance has drawn accusations of antisemitism and activism from critics.
byline: Allan Kaval,  Benjamin Barthe and  Madjid Zerrouky

description: In 50 years, the 8th arrondissement of the French capital, home to the Champs-Elysées and the 'Golden Triangle,' has lost nearly half its population. The mass acquisition of real estate by ultra-wealthy foreigners has driven locals out.

headline: France's best art exhibitions this fall, in Paris and beyond
description: Here is Le Monde's selection of must-see art exhibitions, from painter John Singer Sargent to medieval forgeries to contemporary Nigerian artist Otobong Nkanga, which will go on display through the end of the year.

headline: Qatar owns 20% of property on Paris' Champs-Elysées
description: By reviewing land registry records, Le Monde determined that one-fifth of the facades on Paris's prestigious avenue are owned by the small Gulf monarchy.
